<br>
Remember, it works ALL the time, not just during fights.<br>
<br>
Average spider in velks takes 1500hps to kill. Fungi = 6 extra mobs per hour, or ~33% increase in exp.<br>
<br>
Hps = safety, and difficulty of mob<br>
but<br>
Regen = kill rate.<br>
<br>
<br>
All else being equal, a monk with 2.5k hps and fungi will exp much faster than a monk with 4.5k hps and no fungi.<br>
<br>
However, give both a fungi (or both without) and they will exp at EXACTLY the same rate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulizzardlee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lizzardlee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 625<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/14/02 5:52:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11803.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ok</span><hr size=1> Yes but What about Fungi VS. DPS? Yeah thats alot of hp regened per hour however how much hp per hour am I saving by killing X mob faster because of the upgrade to my dps? I'm not rich so I can't have a fungi AND an epic/hp/ac/resists. Small guild so I can only get a low 50's group together once and awhile to camp KC and can't do chardok at all. Not going to leave guild however I can toss together guildies/friends/friends of friends for 1 time final fight type deal.  <p>54 Disciple of Cazic Thule - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87708">Lizzardlee Blitzfizt</a><br>
