<br>
People constantly say &quot;but, I have a cleric in my group (always), and so I don't need the regen&quot;. But even if you do, they may be healing someone else, or be dead, or OOM, or OOR. I can assure you that a Fungi is absolutly invaluable in these situations. Add in MEND, First Aid AA skill, and I often need no healing on a raid at all.<br>
<br>
Fungi is NOT a solo'ing only item. In a long fight, where I get riposted every now and then, get turned on every now and then, get AoE damage, Fungi is a live saver.<br>
<br>
Add in MEND on a long fight as well, and I'm often the one left standing when everyone else has slowly been &quot;eaten&quot; away bit by bit.<br>
<br>
And as to it's low AC, or low saves. Well, my AC is over 1300 raid buffed, so I'm over the soft cap. When figting AoE mobs, all relevant resists are over 250 anyway with buffs and bards AoE songs... or it's an unresistable AoE. <p><br>
